rComments: Engaging and inspirational. Be sure to know your micro theory and econometrics though.

The hardest course I ever took in my 4 years BUT I left inspired! Some of the material was very interesting but a lot was tough. I wasn't expecting having to memorize complex formulae. Tests were hard. Reading the material BEFORE class is likely important to follow along or you will be confused (as I usually was). Prof is very helpful one-on-one.

I LOVE this course. It is one of the few Econ courses at U of T that goes into public/development areas without dumbing it down in terms of economic theory. The prof is so friendly and so willing to help you and to know you. A challenging course, but a rewarding and eye-opening one. Prof speaks with great knowledge in this field.

ECO324 is the hardest course ever.(!!!) Lots of reading, lots of notes,and the tests are not based on textbook nor problem set(I think~).Besides,there's a 15% participation mark, it means u have to ask questions in class, and there are 10 in-class quizes, each worth 2 point!
I agree. This class is not easy at all, but he helps you if you talk to him at his office. I've been doing that and hopefully will do better in the final.

When I registered for this course, I didn't know what I was getting myself into. This is the hardest course I've taken, and this is my fourth year and I'm getting my B.A. in econ... He doesn't explain the material very well, and neither does his lectures relate to what he tests. I just he's not back next fall, for the sake of my fellow students.
